<grammar>
<section>
<title> Personal pronouns and possessive adjectives</title>
<sectiontitle> We use &lt;i&gt;I&lt;/i&gt; + verb and &lt;i&gt;my&lt;/i&gt; + noun. We usually use the short form, &lt;i&gt;I'm&lt;/i&gt;.</sectiontitle>
<titlesound>sta_gram1_1_1.mp3</titlesound>
<text1></text1>
<text1a>&lt;b&gt;I'm&lt;/b&gt; a student. &lt;b&gt;My&lt;/b&gt; name's Alison.</text1a>
<sound1>sta_gram1_1_2.mp3</sound1>
<sectiontitle2>We use &lt;i&gt;you&lt;/i&gt; + verb and &lt;i&gt;your&lt;/i&gt; + noun.</sectiontitle2>
<titlesound2>sta_gram1_1_3.mp3</titlesound2>
<text3></text3>
<text3a>&lt;b&gt;You&lt;/b&gt;'re a teacher. &lt;b&gt;Your&lt;/b&gt; name is Mrs Adams.</text3a>
<sound3>sta_gram1_1_4.mp3</sound3>
</section>
<section>
<title> Personal pronouns and possessive adjectives</title>
<sectiontitle>We use &lt;i&gt;he +&lt;/i&gt; verb and &lt;i&gt;his +&lt;/i&gt; noun&lt;i&gt;. &lt;/i&gt;We usually use the short form, &lt;i&gt;he's.&lt;/i&gt;</sectiontitle>
<titlesound>sta_gram1_1_5.mp3</titlesound>
<text1></text1>
<text1a>&lt;b&gt;He's&lt;/b&gt; a student. &lt;b&gt;His&lt;/b&gt; name's Stephen.</text1a>
<sound1>sta_gram1_1_6.mp3</sound1>
<text2></text2>
<text2a></text2a>
<sound2></sound2>
<sectiontitle2>We use &lt;i&gt;she +&lt;/i&gt; verb and &lt;i&gt;her +&lt;/i&gt; noun. We usually use the short form &lt;i&gt;she's&lt;/i&gt;.</sectiontitle2>
<titlesound2>sta_gram1_1_7.mp3</titlesound2>
<text3> </text3>
<text3a>&lt;b&gt;She's&lt;/b&gt; an actress. &lt;b&gt;Her&lt;/b&gt; name's Jodie.</text3a>
<sound3>sta_gram1_1_8.mp3</sound3>
<text4></text4>
<text4a></text4a>
<sound4></sound4>
</section>
</grammar>